      },
      "date": "2023-09-26 08:48:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Andreas, should count be reseted by some timer or lfsck start? With\n > a high uptime stack would not be repeated even after month.\n\nIt could be changed from just a one-time check to \"print once a day\" or similar, if you think that is important:\n\n        static time_t print_next;\n\n        if (ktime_get_seconds() > print_next) {\n                print_next = ktime_get_seconds() + 24 * 3600;\n                dump_stack();\n        }\n\nNote that this is only affecting the stack trace, the error message itself is rate limited but would still be printed every 10 minutes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
